== Introduction == <!--T:1-->

<!--T:2-->
In FreeCAD the word "[[Datum|Datum]]" is normally used to refer to auxiliary geometry that is not part of the final [[Shape|Shape]] of the [[Model|model]], but used as a reference and support for [[Sketch|sketches]] and other objects. Datums can be used in all workbenches. Some objects, such as a [[Std_Part|Std Part]], a [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]] and an [[Assembly_CreateAssembly|Assembly]], contain a coordinate system (Origin) by default.

<!--T:3-->
The datums are derived from [[App_GeoFeature|App GeoFeature]]:
* [[Part_CoordinateSystem|Part CoordinateSystem]]
* [[Part_DatumPlane|Part DatumPlane]]
* [[Part_DatumLine|Part DatumLine]]
* [[Part_DatumPoint|Part DatumPoint]]

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Switch to the [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign Workbench]].
# Press {{Button|[[File:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]]}}.
# Select the Origin of the Body, and make it visible by pressing the {{KEY|Space}} bar on your keyboard.
# Press {{Button|[[File:Part_DatumPlane.svg|16px]] [[Part_DatumPlane|Part DatumPlane]]}} to open the Attachment [[Task_Panel|task panel]].
# In the [[3D_View|3D View]], click on one of the standard planes, for example, the XY-plane. Then press {{Button|OK}} to close the task panel.
# Now in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]], select the newly created DatumPlane, and then press {{Button|[[File:PartDesign_NewSketch.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_NewSketch|PartDesign NewSketch]]}}.
# Create a closed wire, and then use {{Button|[[File:PartDesign_Pad.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Pad|PartDesign Pad]]}} to extrude the sketch, and create an initial solid.

<!--T:7-->
Now you can move and rotate the DatumPlane as you wish, by changing its properties in the [[Property_View|Property View]], and the Sketch and Pad will follow its new [[Placement|Placement]].

<!--T:8-->
You can add other types of datums to be used with other sketches and features.


